"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-paralympics-paralympics-tickets-paris-2024-b2600746.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  The host city emptied during the Olympic Games earlier in the summer but bumper crowds are expected for the Paralympics  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Parisians are the main buyers of tickets for theParalympics, organisers said, rushing to grab a second opportunity to see competitions in some of the Games' spectacular venues, after many chose to snub theOlympicsor missed out on tickets.\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In July, Parisians hadleft the city in drovesahead of the Olympics, with entire neighbourhoods turned eerily quiet as residents decamped as they feared the disturbance and traffic problems many thought the Games would bring.\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 931, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Games turned out to be a global success.\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paralympics will allow them to see Olympic sports in the same venues, includingat the feet of the Eiffel Toweror in the gardens of theVersailles castle outside Paris.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1146, \"end\": 1151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.1969771231954086e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers said that of the more than1.75m tickets already soldahead of the August 28 start of the Paralympics, 92% came from French buyers, with buyers from the Ile-de-France region around Paris taking the lion's share of 73%.\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1280, \"end\": 1286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5992804490952662, \"rank\": 0.5518303579273086, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1316, \"end\": 1336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00cele-de-France\", \"score\": 0.999999999979309, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ile-de-France region\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00cele-de-France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00cele-de-France\"}, {\"begin\": 1344, \"end\": 1349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.1969771231954086e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Parisian Mathieu Bucella is set to boost these numbers a little further.\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1455, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am seriously thinking about it because I am a bit annoyed that I did not think of getting tickets for the [Olympic] Games, so this is my second chance,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers said several sessions were nearly sold out already, notably wheelchair fencing and para taekwondo in Grand Palais, para track cycling in Saint Quentin, para equestrian in Chateau de Versailles and blind football at Champ de Mars.\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1771, \"end\": 1784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Quentin\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.532307736449846e-13, \"text\": \"Saint Quentin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Quentin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Quentin\"}, {\"begin\": 1805, \"end\": 1826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chateau de Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We were watching the Olympic Games on TV, but after that you get that gut feeling that you want to come and see everything with your own eyes,\\\" Mexican tourist Arlet Haro said.\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 2042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2010, \"end\": 2017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"score\": 0.9974530436222239, \"rank\": 0.0025102746274381785, \"text\": \"Mexican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"US tourist Asad Rahman said he was glad to have come to Paris for the Paralympics.\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2044, \"end\": 2046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9495154127559, \"rank\": 0.053166351508156545, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2055, \"end\": 2059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad_Asad\", \"score\": 0.9988756335166644, \"rank\": 0.001125371193007671, \"text\": \"Asad\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2566598\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad_Asad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad_Asad\"}, {\"begin\": 2060, \"end\": 2066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A._R._Rahman\", \"score\": 0.9999999643803228, \"rank\": 3.561924641333606e-08, \"text\": \"Rahman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A._R._Rahman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A._R._Rahman\"}, {\"begin\": 2100, \"end\": 2105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.1969771231954086e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Things are a little bit more open than what we heard with the Olympics, where they closed off some areas.\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So it works out, as a tourist,\\\" he said by the Eiffel Tower, where workers were converting the beach volleyball pitch into a blind football pitch.\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heavy security during the Olympics made movement across the city center difficult as many key thoroughfares were blocked.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paralympicswill run until September 8.\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Reuters  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 2550, \"to\": 2789, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2550, \"end\": 2557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999992824087, \"rank\": 4.229266282893125e-10, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 2610, \"end